= Our downloads =

== For~end~users ==

These options are for~everybody who needs LUWRAIN for~work. 
With~the~list below, you can find a~binary distribution prepared for~OS you have already installed or 
a~ISO-image suitable for running LUWRAIN as~a~stand-alone OS (in~this~case no~installed OS required).

=== Choose the~most suitable form you need: ===

* [local:iso/ 
Bootable ISO-images] (installed OS isn't required)

* Binary distributions as~applications:

** [local:windows/
For~Microsoft Windows]

** [local:linux/
For~GNU/Linux]

== For~developers and testers ==

The~first option of~this list is purposed for~the~developers
of~applications for~LUWRAIN.
Others can be~useful only for~developers who would like to~improve LUWRAIN itself.

* [local:sdk/
LUWRAIN~SDK] 
(needed for~building your own application for~LUWRAIN)

* [local:git/
Git~repositories]
(the~entire set of~repositories for~tracking of~changes in~our~project)

* [tarball/
Tarballs with source materials]
(published basically to~make LUWRAIN sources downloadable in~single click,
but there is a~tarball with~media files which we don't put~in~Git repositories)

* [local:nightly/
Nightly builds]
(regular binary builds for~testers)

{NOTE!} You may visit the~host [http://download.luwrain.org download.luwrain.org] directly 
as~a~single and easily observable place gathering all of~our~materials for~download.
Besides all, you can find there:

* [http://download.luwrain.org/pdf/ Our PDF materials (publications and presentations)]
* [http://download.luwrain.org/chats/ Talks in~radio and podcasts (mostly in~Russian)]
* [http://download.luwrain.org/video/ Video recordings (mostly in~Russian)]

